review_blob: Weak and watery,another lager for a hot summer day in Jamaica, not London,had it recently during the Cannibal corpse gig in Camden , it was one out of 3 choices of beer during the venue.

Weak and very overrated beer ,nothing special,its ok to have one or two cans after work,but its a beer drink,my off licence does 6 for 5 deal, so I buy it once in a while,in my opinion its a bit weak for the belgs
Very nice, always buy it in our local Weatherspoons,sparkly yellow,has a mild oakey taste to it,not bad at all.
beer_name: Westons Oak Conditioned Medium Sweet Cider

review_blob: This one could turn into a bad experience, very sweet and fully chemicalised,pumped with alcohol and hell knows what else,I'd rather have a cup of tea
Probably one of the better english ciders,despite the amount of alcohol goes down well if cold,not as bubbly as strongbow,oakey flavour,pretty dry.Good

Very dry and madly carbonated yellow looking cider, I used to drink a lot of it in covent garden while watching live rockabilly band on sunday,getting headaches soon after too ,1 or 2 cans-not bad for a hot summer day though.
Worse cider than this one simply doesn't exist,strong smell of chemicals,horrible aftertaste and  toxic hangover
Easy to drink although rich in alcohol,full of flavour and goes well with food,will have again for sure
Nice white head remains all the way through,misty amber,a bit sour/bitter finish and lack of taste-glad I tried this one but thats about it
Dark and cloudy beer ,very rich in taste ,well hidden alcohol,kind of heavy and sour at the end, not bad after all but wouldn't drink a lot of this stuff
